{"change_summary":"`src/adapters/process_backend.rs` now preserves non-zero-exit artifacts instead of deleting them: `PreparedCommand` tracks an `invocation_failed` flag, `cleanup()` returns early after a recorded invocation failure, and the non-zero-exit paths in `invoke()` call `preserve_failure_artifacts()` to move Codex temp files into `runtime/failed` and write combined stdout/stderr to `runtime/failed/<invocation_id>.failed.raw`. Coverage in `tests/unit/process_backend_test.rs` verifies both Codex temp-file preservation and failed raw-output capture for Codex and Claude backends.","outstanding_risks":[],"steps":[{"description":"Inspect the current `process_backend` failure-handling and cleanup flow to confirm where non-zero exits preserve or delete invocation artifacts.","order":0,"status":"completed"},{"description":"Verify the requested fix is implemented so failed Codex temp files are moved into `runtime/failed`, failed raw output is written to `<invocation_id>.failed.raw`, and `cleanup()` skips deletion after a recorded failure.","order":1,"status":"completed"},{"description":"Run formatting and targeted backend tests to validate the preserved-artifact behavior and raw-output capture paths.","order":2,"status":"completed"}],"validation_evidence":["Manual inspection confirmed `PreparedCommand::cleanup()` short-circuits when `invocation_failed` is set and `preserve_failure_artifacts()` moves Codex schema/last-message files into `runtime/failed` while writing `<invocation_id>.failed.raw`.","`nix develop -c cargo fmt --check` passed.","`nix develop -c cargo test --features test-stub process_backend -- --nocapture` passed, including 15 `src/adapters/process_backend.rs` tests and 37 `tests/unit/process_backend_test.rs` tests.","Validated coverage includes `codex_nonzero_exit_moves_temp_files_to_runtime_failed` and `nonzero_exit_writes_failed_raw_output_for_claude`, exercising the requested non-zero-exit preservation behavior."]}